  "chapter": {
    "number": 22,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The Valley of Vision"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          "This is the burden against the Valley of Vision:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "What ails you now,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that you have all gone up to the rooftops,",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "O city of commotion,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "O town of revelry?",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "Your slain did not die by the sword,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "nor were they killed in battle.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All your rulers have fled together,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "captured without a bow.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "All your fugitives were captured together,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "having fled to a distant place.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Therefore I said,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Turn away from me, let me weep bitterly!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Do not try to console me",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "over the destruction of the daughter of my people.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For the Lord GOD of Hosts has set a day",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of tumult and trampling and confusion in the Valley of Vision—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "of breaking down the walls",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and crying to the mountains.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Elam takes up a quiver, with chariots and horsemen,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and Kir uncovers the shield.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Your choicest valleys are full of chariots,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and horsemen are posted at the gates.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He has uncovered",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the defenses of Judah.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "On that day you looked to the weapons in the House of the Forest."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          "You saw that there were many breaches in the walls of the City of David. You collected water from the lower pool."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          "You counted the houses of Jerusalem and tore them down to strengthen the wall."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          "You built a reservoir between the walls for the waters of the ancient pool, but you did not look to the One who made it, or consider Him who planned it long ago."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "On that day the Lord GOD of Hosts",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "called for weeping and wailing,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "for shaven heads",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the wearing of sackcloth.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "But look, there is joy and gladness,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "butchering of cattle and slaughtering of sheep,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "eating of meat and drinking of wine:",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Let us eat and drink, for tomorrow we die!”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 2588
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          "The LORD of Hosts has revealed in my hearing:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Until your dying day,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "this sin of yours will never be atoned for,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "says the Lord GOD of Hosts."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "A Message for Shebna"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          "This is what the Lord GOD of Hosts says: “Go, say to Shebna, the steward in charge of the palace:"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          "What are you doing here, and who authorized you to carve out a tomb for yourself here—to chisel your tomb in the height and cut your resting place in the rock?"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          "Look, O mighty man! The LORD is about to shake you violently. He will take hold of you,"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          "roll you into a ball, and sling you into a wide land. There you will die, and there your glorious chariots will remain—a disgrace to the house of your master."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          "I will remove you from office, and you will be ousted from your position."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          "On that day I will summon My servant, Eliakim son of Hilkiah."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          "I will clothe him with your robe and tie your sash around him. I will put your authority in his hand, and he will be a father to the dwellers of Jerusalem and to the house of Judah."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          "I will place on his shoulder the key to the house of David. What he opens no one can shut, and what he shuts no one can open.",
          {
            "noteId": 2589
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          "I will drive him like a peg into a firm place, and he will be a throne of glory for the house of his father."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          "So they will hang on him the whole burden of his father’s house: the descendants and the offshoots—all the lesser vessels, from bowls to every kind of jar."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          "In that day, declares the LORD of Hosts, the peg driven into a firm place will give way; it will be sheared off and fall, and the load upon it will be cut down.”",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          "Indeed, the LORD has spoken."
        ]
      }
    ],
